  "text": "To calculate DBA, we converted accelerometer measures from m/s 2 to g (1 g = 9.81 m/s 2 ). We used a 2 s running mean of the raw acceleration data to calculate static acceleration (gravitational acceleration) and subtracted the static acceleration from the raw acceleration data to calculate dynamic acceleration [CITATION_1] . We calculated ODBA as the absolute sum of dynamic acceleration across the 3 axes [CITATION_2] .",
